column7: 2017 UWOYT Trial @ Winnsboro, LA. Notes: Wet and very warm winter with prolonged periods of saturated soils during the winter months as well as heavy rains after maturity; ~50-0-0+S topdress N as 32% liquid in mid February and 25-0-0 in late February; severe lodging in all plots from storms and heavy disease (crown + stem rust) pressure contributed to high yield CV and low yields/ test wts; plants in plots were picked up off of the ground by the combine resutling in harvest efficiency variation.
